01/10/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The foreign ministry said Thursday (30 September) it is open to talks with Slovene counterparts on ways to resolve border issues. 
Another incident took place at the maritime border in the Savudrija Bay. 
Zagreb says two boats with Slovene policemen and a nautical inspector entered Croatian territorial waters Thursday and warned Croatian fishermen that they were in Slovene waters. 
The two neighbours have argued over border areas since the dissolution of the former Yugoslav federation.
In other news Thursday, Croatia signed an agreement with Morocco on mutual stimulation and protection of investments. 
Croatia also plans to sign an agreement with Austria on co-operation in culture and education. 
(HINA, HRT - 30/09/04)
